    q: 'What is AgRP?',
    a: 'Agouti-related peptide (AgRP) is the body’s built-in hunger signal. It is made by a specific set of neurons in the hypothalamus and works by blocking the melanocortin "I am full" signal at the MC4R and MC3R receptors, tilting the balance toward eating.',
